"title": "8654: importunity, towards people",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8654: importunity, towards people",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Boldness, urgency and persistence in appealing to others; seen in making requests of all kinds, presenting the gospel and giving Christian instruction; seen too in God's patient and persistent pleading with people.</p>\n<h2>Making requests of others</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:3\">GEN 19:3</a> <em>Lot prevails on his angelic visitors to stay with him</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:10\">GEN 39:10</a> <em>Potiphar's wife propositions Joseph</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:37\">NUM 22:37</a> <em>Balak summons Balaam</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg14:16-Judg14:17\">JDG 14:16–14:17</a> <em>Samson's wife presses for the answer to his riddle</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:6-Judg16:16\">JDG 16:6–16:16</a> <em>Delilah nags Samson to know the secret of his strength</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs2:16-2Kgs2:17\">2KI 2:16–2:17</a> <em>Elisha is requested to authorise a search for Elijah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:3-Esth3:4\">EST 3:3–3:4</a> <em>Royal officials plead with Mordecai</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth8:3\">EST 8:3</a> <em>Esther pleads with the king</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:7\">PRO 19:7</a> <em>A poor man pleads in vain with fair-weather friends</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:26\">JER 38:26</a> <em>Jeremiah pleads with King Zedekiah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:23\">LUK 23:23</a> <em>The crowds call for Jesus Christ to be crucified</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:16\">ACT 12:16</a> <em>Peter knocks on the door after his release from prison</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts25:3\">ACT 25:3</a> <em>The chief priests urge that Paul be taken to Jerusalem</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:4\">2CO 8:4</a> <em>The Macedonian churches ask to share in the giving to God's people</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:2\">PHP 4:2</a> <em>Paul pleads with Euodia and Syntyche to agree.</em></p>\n<h2>Importunity in preaching the gospel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:20\">2CO 5:20</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Persistence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:42\">ACT 5:42</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Urgent appeal</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:40\">ACT 2:40</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Boldness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:8\">ACT 19:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:29\">ACT 4:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:31\">ACT 4:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:27\">ACT 9:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:3\">ACT 14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:26\">ACT 18:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:31\">ACT 28:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:14\">PHP 1:14</a></p>\n<h3>Persuasion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:11\">2CO 5:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:4\">ACT 18:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:8\">ACT 19:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:28\">ACT 26:28</a></p>\n<h2>Importunity in giving instruction</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:1\">2CO 10:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:1\">1TH 4:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:15\">ROM 15:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:43\">ACT 13:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:1\">2CO 6:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:12\">GAL 4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:1\">EPH 4:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:17\">EPH 4:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:10\">1TH 4:10</a></p>\n<h2>God's persistent appeal</h2>\n<h3>God's repeated call to individuals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam3:8\">1SA 3:8</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:17\">JHN 21:17</a></strong></p>\n<h3>God's appeal to his wayward people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:15\">2CH 36:15</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:13\">JER 7:13</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:35-Matt21:37\">MAT 21:35–21:37</a></strong> <em>Finally, God sends his Son.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:25\">JER 7:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:7\">JER 11:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:3-Jer25:4\">JER 25:3–25:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer26:5\">JER 26:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer29:19\">JER 29:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:33\">JER 32:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer35:14-Jer35:15\">JER 35:14–35:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:4\">JER 44:4</a></p>",
